s includes ensuring that the AI Technology used and the provider of that AI Technology does not gain any rights over the author’s underlying content, including the right to “train” their AI Technology on the content, besides the limited right to access and use the submission to perform the service. By reviewing an AI Technology’s terms and conditions for clauses such as “ownership,” “data reuse,” or “opt out” among others, authors can prevent unintended rights transfers.\n\nResponsible and Ethical Use\nAuthors must use AI Technology in a manner that aligns with privacy, confidentiality, and compliance obligations\n------------------------\noutput:\n(\"entity\"<|>WILEY<|>PUBLISHER<|>Wiley is a publisher of academic journals and is committed to ethical publishing and integrity)\n##\n(\"entity\"<|>AUTHOR<|>AUTHOR<|>An individual who writes and submits research for publication, and must adhere to Wiley's policies on AI use and disclosure)\n##\n(\"entity\"<|>AI TECHNOLOGY<|>AI TECHNOLOGY<|>A system or tool that uses artificial intelligence to assist in writing, editing, or generating content, which authors must disclose and use responsibly)\n##\n(\"entity\"<|>TRANSPARENCY<|>TRANSPARENCY<|>A principle emphasized by Wiley to ensure ethical publishing and integrity, requiring authors to disclose the use of AI technology)\n##\n(\"entity\"<|>ETHICAL USE<|>ETHICAL USE<|>The responsible and appropriate application of AI technology by authors, aligned with privacy, confidentiality, and compliance obligations)\n##\n(\"entity\"<|>RIGHTS PROTECTION<|>POLICY<|>A policy set by Wiley that requires authors to ensure AI technology does not restrict their or Wiley's rights over the submission)\n##\n(\"entity\"<|>PEER REVIEW PROCESS<|>PEER REVIEW PROCESS<|>The process through which manuscripts are evaluated by experts before publication, which may request additional information about AI use)\n##\n(\"entity\"<|>SUBMISSION<|>MANUSCRIPT<|>A manuscript submitted to a Wiley journal, which may 